{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"1. AN INTRODUCTION TO YACHT BROKERAGE"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The primary purpose of this first module is to introduce the reader to the many aspects that collectively make up what"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"can be referred to as the yacht brokerage industry. The module is intended to be general in its nature, that is to say it will"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"touch upon many different topics and cover none to any great depth. For readers who are familiar in whole, or in part,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"with the yacht brokerage industry much of what follows will be familiar. However, all of the following has been prepared"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"with the yacht broker and retailer in mind and therefore should provide some insight into their role and the work they"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"are likely to do."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"What is a Yacht Brokerage?"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The first question that needs to be addressed is exactly what is a yacht or a small craft? Strictly speaking there is no formal"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"definition of such a craft as designation often relates to the function to which the vessel will be used. However, for the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"purposes of this module a yacht or small craft is taken to mean any vessel whether commercial or private pleasure that"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"does not carry passengers."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"A small wooden sailing dinghy and a large modern motor cruiser"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"For this module the author has drawn mainly on his experience of the United Kingdom yacht industry. Whilst this is an"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"industry that has been established for over a hundred years it is not meant to imply that this is the only way for an industry,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"particular parts of the industry or indeed individuals to behave. A study of the United Kingdom model will be applicable,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"in part, to much of the world. However, there are also significant differences (cultural, legal and ethical) between countries"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"and the student would be well advised to seek clarification of detail for different countries (applicable to the individual)"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"as appropriate."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Module 1"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"6"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Structure of the Yacht Brokerage Industry"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As with any industry grouping there are many different parts involved. The following overview of the different functions"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of the industry is not necessarily exhaustive or mutually exclusive. Frequently there is a significant cross over between"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"different parts of the industry with individuals often fulfilling more than one specific function."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The designer"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"All waterborne craft need to start somewhere and invariably it is in the mind\u2019s eye of the designer. Such an individual may"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"be an enthusiastic amateur who dreams of building his own yacht from scratch or it may be the senior designer in the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"design office of a design house or a production yacht builder."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"It is the designer\u2019s role to come up with the initial concept of what the yacht is going to look like and what it is going to"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"achieve. Clearly the design requirements can vary enormously from that of a round the world ocean racing yacht to a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"small robust harbour workboat."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"When considering design it is not just the exterior \u201cstyling\u201d that is considered i.e. what it looks like when on the water, but"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"also the space utilisation and ergonomics of both the internal and external spaces."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Depending upon the particular designer, his role may be to develop the concept that is then passed to a Naval Architect"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"to translate to a set of functional plans or it may be to develop the entire concept from idea to reality. Design can be artistic"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"or functional always depending upon the intent behind the original idea."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Having developed a set of pictures and plans that represents what the yacht is going to look like the designer may now"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"turn to somebody to translate those plans into a physical reality."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The naval architect"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Naval Architect is the person who generally converts the idea of the Designer into a set of drawings and specification"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"from which the craft can be built. Often the Designer and the Naval Architect will be one and the same person but this is"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"by no means exclusively the case."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Naval Architects tend to work with numbers. They define the structure of the yacht in terms of its physical strength, its"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"performance in terms of speed and power and its degree of stability i.e. just how well it will stay upright. The work will"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"generally involve input from others such as the Rules of a Classification Society, national (such as the British Standards"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Institute) or indeed international (the International Organisation for Standardisation) minimum requirements. In some"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"cases (normally small craft used for commercial purposes) there are statutory regulations to comply with whilst for leisure"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"only craft there are statutory European Regulations that relate to the standards for a vessel sold within the European Union."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The end result of the Naval Architect\u2019s work is generally a set of detailed drawings which show all the parts of the yacht,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"both structure and systems, together with a technical specification which details the functional and\/or performance"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"requirements of every part of the yacht. With this information, the yacht moves one step closer to completion."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"A Naval Architect\u2019s Office"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"7"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The builder"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Builder is the entity that takes the plans of the Naval Architect and converts them into the finished vessel."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As for the Designer a yacht builder can vary from a home build by an amateur to a production yacht forming one of a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"number of virtually identical vessels. The builder will take the plans and starting from nothing will physically produce the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"yacht from a range of different materials and sub systems."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The actual building process will vary depending upon the type of material from which the yacht is to be built. However,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"generally the builder will produce the hull, install major equipment inside, fit the deck and superstructure and then outfit"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"both inside and outside."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As one might expect, building is a crucial time in the life of the yacht. As for all things, the amount of time, effort and"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"expense that goes into the building of yacht will determine the quality. This \u2018in turn\u2019 will translate both into the perceived"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"value and also to the degree of difficulty in selling the yacht in the future."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In the yacht industry of today, yacht building or yacht production has developed into a very advanced and sophisticated"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"sector of the industry turning over many millions of pounds and producing many thousands of boats every year. However,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"this does not mean that all sea going vessels built today are mass produced. Many individuals commission customised"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"boats whilst other build at home from scratch or purchase the basic hull and complete the craft as a home build. In reality"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the market is as diverse as the mind of any individual."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The sheer diversity of craft is one of the problems that a broker is faced with on a daily basis. There are many thousands"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of different types of yacht built by a huge range of different builders over a long period of time. Some are well established"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"with good reputations, some are well established with bad reputations, some only ever build one or two craft. The"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"practising broker needs an appreciation of the degree of diversity whilst recognising that they can never know everything"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"there is to know about all the different yachts."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Having built the yacht, the next step is to find somebody who desires the particular vessel sufficiently in order to buy it."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Several different types of builders\u2019 boatyards"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Module 1"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"8"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The yacht broker"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"It is the yacht broker\u2019s task to bring the person selling a boat, whether new or second hand, and a prospective purchaser"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"together in such a way that a deal can be struck and the boat Ownership transferred."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The yacht broker will generally have been approached by a potential vendor (the seller of the yacht) and will establish the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"details of the yacht in terms of its physical dimensions and material description. It is his job to present the yacht in the best"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"possible manner in order to attract potential buyers to come and look at it. In doing this the yacht broker will generally"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"establish the title of the yacht i.e. whether or not the vendor is the legal Owner with the right to sell and he may also act"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"as the Owner\u2019s agent in arranging for viewing and negotiating the sale."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In the retail environment the yacht broker represents the builder or the builder\u2019s sale organisation and will be selling a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"boat that is new and the details of which are (or should be) well known to him."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"It is important to remember that the broker represents the interests of the vendor and not the buyer. Therefore, the broker"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"will be focused on ensuring that the price paid is as high as possible as this serves the interest of his client. Frequently,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"although not exclusively, the broker will only be paid (the commission) on successful completion of a sale and this is"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"something that can lead to potential problems if it is not fully appreciated at an early stage."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"It should also be remembered that the broker is not a technical expert. Whilst many good brokers have extensive"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"knowledge of types of boats and their particular advantages and disadvantages as well as excellent knowledge of the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"various physical aspects of a boat, it is not their job to be a technical expert. Sometimes this can lead to problems when a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"broker finds out from a potential buyer (via a survey report) that the yacht he is offering for sale is not all that he believed"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"it to be or when defects are identified with a new boat of which he was unaware."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As stated previously it is the broker\u2019s role to represent the best interests of the vendor, whether this is the Owner of a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"private yacht or a builder."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As with other parts of the yacht brokerage industry, brokers can work as small companies (one-man bands) or form part"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of a very large company with many employees."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"A yacht broker\u2019s office in a large marina"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"9"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The owner"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In effect, it is the Owner who is the driving force behind the whole of the yacht brokerage industry. Without Owners there"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"would be no need for any of the other functions. Fortunately, however, there are many Owners with the desire to purchase"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a yacht or small craft in order to get afloat."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As with all things in the yacht industry there is a huge range of differences between Owners. Some are very wealthy and"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"buy luxurious yachts costing millions whilst some will go yachting on the smallest of budgets. In any event, one thing of"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"which the broker can be certain is that the Owner will generally be totally in love with his boat. Boat Ownership is about"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"passion and the prospective broker needs to understand that what might appear to be an ugly little tub to him is in fact"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a dream boat to the person wishing to buy it."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Owners need not be individuals. The legal title holder could be a company (body corporate) or a finance organisation that"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"has a contract with an individual (or company) such that the finance organisation remains the legal Owner until such time"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"as the loan for the craft has been repaid. In any event the broker needs an appreciation that the Owner may not necessarily"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"be the person or organisation that represents themselves to be so."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The finance organisation"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As yachts have become more and more luxurious and the cost to buy has increased, it has become far more common"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"for banks and financial institutions to lend money in order for an Owner to purchase the yacht. Loans normally take one"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of two forms, secured and unsecured."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"An unsecured loan is in effect a contract between the finance organisation and the Owner and does not specifically"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"concern the craft. The finance organisation lends the money to the Owner who, in effect, promises (in a contract) to pay"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"it back. Therefore, in the case of an unsecured loan the lender is generally not interested in whether the craft is purchased"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"or not. These types of loan were common up until 2009 but with a significant slowing down of the world economy and"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"many banks having problems with bad debt (a small proportion of which would have come from the yacht industry) such"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"loans are not quite so readily available these days."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"A secured loan, however, means that the lender takes a charge (in effect takes legal title of the yacht) on the craft using"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a contract. The lender agrees to loan the purchaser the money to buy and use the yacht subject to a range of terms and"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"conditions (normally including repayment terms, interest and sometimes insurance)."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As a result the finance organisation will sometimes need an independent opinion as to the value of the yacht as the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"physical value of the craft is the security against which the money is lent. Once again this moves into the territory of"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the broker. Frequently a surveyor who carries out a condition survey will be asked to do a valuation and indeed this is"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"common practice. However, caution is needed here. It is the broker who sells the yacht and, therefore, by definition it is the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"broker who knows, as a matter of fact, what any particular boat was worth at the time of sale (the sale price often being"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"an item of confidential information between vendor, purchaser and broker). This does not mean that a valuation done by"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a surveyor is necessarily wrong, but it does mean that how the valuation is achieved and what it represents potentially"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"becomes very important."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Module 1"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"10"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The insurance company"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Having purchased a yacht, on most occasions the Owner will wish to insure it. In doing so there are two basic types of"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"insurance that will be needed."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Lloyd\u2019s of London Building"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The first is Hull and Machinery insurance. This is the term used to describe the insurance that covers the physical material"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of the yacht, the hull, systems, engines, rig, sails, furnishing and equipment that make up the particular yacht."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The second type of insurance is liability or third party insurance (often call third party liability insurance). This insurance"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"protects against damage done by the boat to other Owner\u2019s boats or to other people and\/or their property."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Neither type of insurance is compulsory for pleasure craft navigating on the high seas. However, third party liability"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"insurance is compulsory in some countries and also in certain circumstances in this country, e.g. for inland waterways in"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"England under the Boat Safety Scheme."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As with all other aspects of the yacht brokerage industry the range of insurance available to an Owner is great. Insurance"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"is normally purchased through an insurance broker who, like the yacht broker, is acting on behalf of his client (the buyer of"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the insurance). Insurance can come from traditional sources such as Lloyd\u2019s of London or from insurance companies. The"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"insurance is a contract between the Underwriter on behalf of the insurance interest and the insured. Marine insurance is"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a special type of contract coming under the Marine Insurance Act that is covered in more detail in a later module of this"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"course."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The insurance will involve the Owner paying a sum of money against the probability of an accident happening that"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"involves the yacht."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Ultimately it is the Underwriter who pays the bill when there has been an incident that leads to damage, provided the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"incident and damage are properly covered by the insurance."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"11"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"One example of yacht damage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The yacht surveyor"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As with the previous groups mentioned, the yacht surveyor comes in many shapes and sizes. Some may specialise in"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"particular sectors of the market e.g. inland waterways craft or wooden yachts whilst many remain generalists providing"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"an independent service to their clients."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Many surveyors operate as one-man bands, some operate as small companies or partnerships and some operate as part"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of a franchise. Whatever the particular method of operation, in all cases it is the knowledge, expertise and attitude of the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"individual undertaking the work that differentiates the excellent surveyor from the average or poor."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"It is important to remember that the surveyor works on behalf of the prospective purchaser and so he is, in some respects,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"on the other side of the negotiating table from the broker."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Survey conditions are not always perfect"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Module 1"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"12"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Moorings and the marina"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Having purchased the boat, an Owner will need somewhere to keep it. For smaller craft that can be stored on trailers they"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"may be kept close to the Owner\u2019s home or in a land based storage facility. However, for larger craft this will often involve"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"finding a berth, often at a marina."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The types of moorings available vary considerably. Many of the large and well established marinas provide extensive"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"facilities with alongside mooring, water, electricity, rubbish disposal, toilets and showers, restaurants, chandlers, repair"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"facilities and security etc. However, this is by no means the only type of mooring available to the boat Owner. Moorings"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"are available between piles or \u201ctrots\u201d, on swinging moorings where the yacht is allowed to weather vane, moorings where"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the yacht is secured bow and stern and some where the mooring dries out between tides leaving the craft high and dry."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Some yachts may be moored \u201cMediterranean\u201d style, anchored by the bow with the stern next to the quayside."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Marinas may also offer lift out facilities for storing yachts ashore over winter for repairs and maintenance."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In some areas where marina berths are scarce and the berths are owned rather than rented the broker can also play a role"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"in providing berths for new Owners."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"A large marina and a mud berth"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Other service providers"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In addition to the above groups that operate within the yacht brokerage industry there are also numerous other service"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"providers that a yacht broker will come across during the course of his work. These include sail makers, mechanics, boat"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"valets, repair yards, riggers, chandlers, yacht charterers, sailing schools and others."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"For the yacht broker other service providers can provide a valuable source of information and developing a network of"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"contacts with a wide range of people within the industry will always be an asset."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"13"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"2. YACHTING SAFETY"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As a general rule, there is little positive regulation of pleasure craft in the United Kingdom. However,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"this does not mean that yachts are completely un-regulated and there are a range of rules some"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"compulsory, some voluntary with which craft need to comply."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In terms of yacht safety there are a range of different organisations which fulfil different safety functions"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"and these are detailed below."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Flag State"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Flag State is the term used to describe the country to which the craft belongs. In commercial shipping terms this will"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"mean the country where the ship is registered. However, in the United Kingdom registration (i.e. registering the title to the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"craft with a government) is not compulsory for leisure craft. Some yacht Owners choose to register their yachts fully under"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the Flag State or in the UK some yacht Owners with a smaller vessel register their yachts on a special small craft register"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"but, as already stated, this is not necessarily compulsory for pleasure craft. Whilst this might initially appear surprising, it is"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"important to remember the tremendous diversity of craft. Registering a superyacht would clearly be an obvious thing to"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"do but should there be a requirement to register every windsurfer, canoe and sailing dinghy? The question of compulsory"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"registration for leisure craft is a debate that has been carried on for several decades and no immediate changes are"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"foreseen in the United Kingdom."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Red Ensign on the stern of a yacht"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In addition to providing registration, the Flag State also sets out the rules and regulations with which the government"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of the country require craft to comply. Generally at an international level the International Maritime Organisation (IMO),"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"part of the United Nations, works to establish minimum acceptable standards for commercial craft on a worldwide basis."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"However, pleasure craft are normally expressly excluded from such requirements. Even though the IMO works to establish"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"such standards they do not have any powers to force any particular country to embrace the regulations. It is left to the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"government of each individual country to introduce regulations through national legislation which the Flag State believes"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"satisfies the IMO requirements. Clearly, this can lead to different interpretations and differing standards. Furthermore,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"having set the standard, the Flag State then needs to police the standard that it has set. To do this many Flag States have"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"marine surveyors who work as government employees to keep a check on the craft registered with that flag. Once again,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"standards can vary enormously with some countries having a fully developed survey and reporting organisation and some"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"having virtually nothing."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Generally private pleasure yachts of less than 400 tons do not have to comply with many of the regulations with the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"exception of rules such as the International Regulations for Preventing Collisions at Sea 1972 and the Safety of Life at Sea"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"(SOLAS) Chapter V. However, the exact requirements do vary from Flag State to Flag State. Of particular importance to note"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"here is that in many countries there is no legal requirement for a yacht to be built to any particular standard or to carry"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"even a minimum amount of safety equipment. In the United Kingdom for example there is no statutory requirement for"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a yacht used only for private pleasure purposes to carry any sort of fire fighting or lifesaving equipment. Another way of"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"putting this is that it is perfectly acceptable to go to sea burn or drown yourself provided it is for pleasure purposes only!"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As already mentioned most Flag States have organisations that act as the controller of the standards of ships and small"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"craft in their territorial waters and\/or registered in their country. In the United Kingdom this function falls to the Maritime"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"and Coastguard Agency."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Module 1"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"14"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Maritime and Coastguard Agency (MCA)"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The MCA, as it is commonly known, is an executive agency of the Department for Transport (DfT). As an executive agency"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"it operates in many ways like an independent company, but the MCA is in effect the maritime police force for the United"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Kingdom."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Maritime and Coastguard Agency is responsible for:"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"1."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Developing, promoting and enforcing high standards of marine safety."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"2."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Minimising loss of life amongst seafarers and coastal users."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"3."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Responding to maritime emergencies 24 hours a day."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"4."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Minimising the risk of pollution of the marine environment from ships and, where pollution occurs, minimising the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"impact on UK interests."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Maritime and Coastguard Agency sets appropriate safety standards for the Inspections & Surveys of UK Flag vessels in"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"order to ensure that they meet high safety standards. The MCA carries out port state control of non-UK ships, investigates"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"and prosecute breaches of merchant shipping legislation and develops and sets ship and seafarer standards through"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"legislation, Marine Notices and Codes of Practice."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In the UK, whilst private pleasure craft are unregulated, numerous categories of yachts are regulated as soon as they"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"become involved in any sort of commercial venture. The regulations that exist are prepared by the MCA and can take a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"number of forms. The traditional route was for an Act of Parliament to be set up and this in turn gave rise to Statutory"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Instruments that were the technical detail that went in support of any particular requirement."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Vessels operating commercially under the British Flag or in British Waters must comply with the Merchant Shipping"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Regulations or an MCA Code of Practice. See these below."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Yellow"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Code of Practice for the Safety of Small Commercial Motor Vessels."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Blue"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Code of Practice for the Safety of Small Commercial Sailing Vessels."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Brown"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Code of Practice for the Safety of Small Workboats and Pilot Boats."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Red"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Code of Practice for the Safety of Small Vessels in Commercial Use for Sport or Pleasure operating from a Nominated"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Departure Point (NDP)."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In addition to these four Codes there are also two others that are not included within the Certifying Authority framework"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"(but are included here for the sake of completeness)."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"LY2 and LY3"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Large Commercial Yacht Code."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Black"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Code of Practice for Vessels Engaged in Oil Recovery Operations."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The Code Vessel Safety Branch, located at MCA headquarters in Southampton, provides policy, interpretation and technical"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"advice on all Codes of Practice for Commercial Vessels. Codes newsletters are used to help distribute useful advice."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In addition to these codes the MCA have published a guidance document that seeks to harmonise the different codes as"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Marine Guidance Note MGN 280 (M) Small Vessels in Commercial Use for Sport of Pleasure, Workboats and Pilot Boats \u2013"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Alternate Construction Standards."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The MCA has a range of surveyors, either nautical, engineering, naval architecture or fishing"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"and some of these surveyors undertake the inspection work necessary for the implementation"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of code requirements. However, the MCA delegates part of its inspection role to third party"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"organisations known as certifying authorities. These certifying authorities are organisations that undertake the inspection"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"work on behalf of the MCA."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"15"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Certifying authorities"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Currently there are 11 certifying authorities in the United Kingdom that are approved to carry out code compliance survey"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"work on behalf of the MCA. The approved organisations are either Classification Societies, professional organisations or"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"private companies. The list of organisations approved by the MCA to carry out inspection work is published in Marine"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Information Note MIN 514 (M)."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"1. Bureau Veritas (BV)"}}
