{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Listing the Yacht"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Before the broker can offer the yacht for sale, it is necessary for the details of the yacht to be collected and the title of the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"yacht to be established."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Detail listings come from a careful inspection of both the documents of the yacht and the yacht itself. The broker will"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"need to collect the yacht\u2019s specification, in terms of dimensions and equipment, as well as determining the appropriate"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"condition in order to describe the yacht correctly. Included within this is also the question of checking compliance with"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the Recreational Craft Directive and the VAT status of the yacht."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Title comes from verifying that the vendor does, in fact, have the right to offer the yacht for sale. The exact process for"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"this will depend greatly upon whether or not the yacht is registered and\/or exactly how good the paper trail is from the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"original builder to the incumbent Owner. However, for the broker this is a vital activity. If a broker were to facilitate a sale"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"for a vendor that did not have legal right to title, and the rightful Owner was subsequently to reclaim the yacht (as would"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"be his legal right) the buyer could try to sue the broker for negligence."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Inspection"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Having found a prospective buyer, the broker needs to spend time to make certain that the yacht is appropriate to"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the needs of the potential new Owner. It is possible that the buyer may require a survey but before this, in order to"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"save everybody\u2019s time and expense it is better to make certain that the prospective Owner carries out his own careful"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"inspection. The broker needs to show the yacht in a balanced light to the prospective Owner. There is no point in trying to"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"hide defects or to make the yacht out to be something it is not. Even an inexperienced new Owner can identify problem"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"areas and this only serves to undermine the sales process by destroying trust."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Generally an inspection should include some form of sea trial (where practical) to confirm that the craft functions as it"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"should and it is important that the broker allows the prospective Owner sufficient time and space for him to evaluate the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"craft pro"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":" perly."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"It is important to keep in mind that working as a broker is about building relationships. If a sale goes well and both the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"vendor and the purchaser are happy, the chances are that the broker has doubled his client base (as the seller may well"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"be looking for a new yacht and the buyer will need to sell at some point in the future). At the inspection stage the broker"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"has the opportunity to demonstrate his knowledge and his integrity and also to build the sort of lasting relationship that"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"successful and experienced brokers enjoy."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Negotiation and Contract"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Negotiation is essentially a matter of offer and counter offer until the time that both parties agree on a figure. At this stage"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the actual terms of the sale normally begin to be considered (although some of these items will also have been considered"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"during the offer stage) and the form of the sale contract is discussed and agreed. Different standard sale contracts exist"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"or the buyer\/seller may wish to use marine solicitors. In either event a contract will be agreed and, it is hoped, signed."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Care is required by the broker during this process to avoid becoming bound into a contract unintentionally. To avoid this,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the broker needs a detailed understanding of the law relating to the formation of contracts and this is covered in detail"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"in a later Module."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The contract will normally make provision for the payment of a deposit including the terms for return of the deposit and"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"may specify a time scale for the buyer to commission a survey. Often, but not always, the standard time period for survey"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"is 14 days."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"If a survey is required the prospective purchaser may well ask the broker for suggestions\/recommendations of a local"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"surveyor to use. Once again, caution is required. If a broker recommends a surveyor there are two pitfalls awaiting the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"unwary. The first is the possibility for a conflict of interest and the second is another potential liability for negligence."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The conflict of interest arises as both broker and surveyor derive financial benefit from the sale transaction but"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"remuneration depends upon different performance criteria. For the broker, the commission payment comes from the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"vendor on successful completion of the sale. For the surveyor, payment comes from the purchaser, normally irrespective"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of the outcome of the intended transaction. Therefore, it is in the broker\u2019s interest that the survey comes out well (few"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"defects or problems) whilst it is in the surveyor\u2019s interest to make certain that he identifies all the defects and problems"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"(so that he is not sued for negligence subsequently). As brokers have the opportunity to suggest\/recommend surveyors"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"to prospective buyers, there is the potential temptation for both the broker and the surveyor to be more accommodating"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"than perhaps they would be if neither of them had a financial interest."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The potential liability for negligence comes if the recommended surveyor does a poor job for his client (the purchaser). In such a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"case the buyer might well look to the broker for compensation if the surveyor does a shoddy job."}}
