{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"One way round this is for the broker to provide a list of all the surveyors working in the area together with a letter stating"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"this together with an exclusion for liability and a statement that the particular ability and\/or skill of the surveyor has not"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"been checked or assessed by the broker. There is, therefore, no liability. Whilst such an approach does not guarantee that a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"potential buyer will not \u201chave a go\u201d at the broker should he prove dissatisfied with the survey, it goes a long way in helping"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"to reduce the possibility of the buyer succeeding."}}
