{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Survey"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"For a pre-purchase survey, the survey instruction to the surveyor should come from the buyer directly (not through the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"broker). When the surveyor receives the instruction specific expectations of what is wanted are discussed between the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"buyer and the surveyor and terms agreed. Frequently, depending upon the type of survey required, the survey may be"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"carried out with the yacht out of the water. Organising and paying for the boat to be lifted out of the water is normally"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the job of the buyer. However, both buyer and broker may pass this task to the surveyor (as the lift out is done so the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"survey can take place and, therefore, is normally organised for the surveyor\u2019s convenience). In such a case, all parties need"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"to be very clear on the terms of the surveyor\u2019s appointment. Remember, the yacht does not yet belong to the buyer (on"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"whose behalf the surveyor is working) and the Owner will be looking for compensation for any damage done to his yacht"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"(through no fault of his own) before completion of the sale. Equally, the broker might be acting as agent for the vendor"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"and, therefore, will be responsible for discharging his responsibilities properly (in terms of organising the lift out). Unless"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"all parties are very clear on whose responsibility (and hence liability) it is problems can arise."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Subject to what has been agreed with the buyer, the object of a pre-purchase survey is normally to identify all defects"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"with the craft that could normally be discovered. It is not the purpose of this module to go into the detailed requirements"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of the survey but suffice to say that this means that most of the craft will need to be opened up and inspected and most"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"or all of the systems tested. The surveyor will need to spend sufficient time on board in order to identify and record all"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the defects properly and will need sufficient skill to interpret what it is he finds in the context of the buyer\u2019s requirements."}}
