{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"On completion of the survey, the surveyor should prepare his report for the potential buyer, preferably within a limited"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"timeframe."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"It is at this point that problems can occur when the surveyor\u2019s report identifies defects (whether warranted or otherwise)"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"that cause the potential buyer to withdraw or to seek a significant price reduction. The actual terms of the withdrawal from"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"the sale contract will depend upon the specifics of the contract and this can on occasion be an area for disagreement"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"and conflict."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"In an ideal world, the survey report should be a balanced and factual report that identifies the various problems and"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"defects found and puts them into the context of the buyer\u2019s specific requirements and the cost significance in the context"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"of the overall value of the vessel. Often, unfortunately, this is not the case."}}
