{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"With the survey report in hand, the buyer is now ready to complete the sale (or possibly walk away). Depending upon"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"what has been identified in the report, renegotiations of the contract may take place to make allowances for previously"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"unknown defects. It is here that a good surveyor can assist with the sale process. If the report is factually accurate and"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"represents the yacht in a fair and balanced manner, both vendor and buyer will be satisfied and the chances of concluding"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a deal increase dramatically."}}
