{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As with most things in modern day society the law is never far away and whilst limited, the same is true for yachts. In this"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"section we will look very briefly at some aspects of English law in areas where the broker is likely to have some contact. A"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"more detailed coverage of the law as it relates to yachts is included in Module 3 \u2013 Registration, Title, Rules and Regulations"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"and Module 4 \u2013 Boat Brokers and the Law."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Merchant Shipping Legislation and Yachts"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As has been stated previously, most regulations that apply to commercial vessels do not apply to yachts provided they are"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"used only for private pleasure purposes."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Some of the aspects of United Kingdom Merchant Shipping law that a broker may come across from time to time follow."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Registration"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"A ship or yacht is normally registered in order to demonstrate who the legitimate Owner is and, therefore, who is"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"responsible for the vessel."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"The UK Register is divided into 4 parts: -"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Part I for merchant ships and pleasure vessels. Registration under this section enables the vessel to be used as security for"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a marine mortgage i.e. the mortgage details are recorded on the Certificate of Registry and noted in the Register at the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Port of Registry so that it can be checked if required."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Part II is for fishing vessels. As for Part I, registration under this section enables the vessel to be used as security for a marine"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"mortgage."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Part III is for small ships (less than 24 metres). This is a simple registration costing \u00a310 and does not require proof of title."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Therefore, it has no use as security for a marine mortgage."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Part IV is for bareboat charter ships which can include yachts."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Specific requirements and limitations are imposed on those persons and organisations that can own a British Registered"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"vessel. Full details of registration are contained in Module 3."}}
