{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As stated in a later Module \u2013 Boat Brokers and the Law will expand greatly on the various aspect of the law of contract."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Tort"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As with contract, the law of tort, when being sued for negligence, has a particular number of aspects, or tests, which"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"determine whether an individual is liable (about which more is also contained in a later Module)."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"As a professional offering a service, the broker is expected to operate at a level of skill and with the degree of care to which"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"other brokers would normally operate. Therefore, if you do a job to the best of your ability and still fail to do something"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"that other averagely skilled brokers would normally do, subject to other requirements, you could well be held liable for"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"negligence. As no broker can be expected to know everything and because clients and their yachts vary so much there"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"is always a real potential for mistakes, particularly when busy or under pressure."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"One final word of warning on the subject of negligence, even with good trading terms and conditions of contract you"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"cannot contract out of your liability in negligence. Therefore, if you get it wrong expect somebody to come after you."}}
