{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"in a totally unsafe condition, a broker, in his professional capacity cannot. In the event of an incident during a sea trial that"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"was reasonably foreseeable, the broker could find himself being held liable in negligence for taking (allowing) the yacht"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"to go to sea."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Before allowing a sea trial the broker must, at the very least, believe the yacht to be in a safe condition, make certain it is"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"provided with adequate safety equipment, make certain it is properly manned by competent crew and ensure that the"}}
