{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Partnerships"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"A partnership is a relationship between two or more people carrying on business together with a view to making a profit."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Partnerships are neither incorporated nor registered. Unlike a company, therefore, a partnership has no separate legal"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"identity. For the purposes of legal transaction or litigation, only the members of the partnership can employ people,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"own property, enter into contracts or be sued. As with sole traders each partner is regarded as liable on a personal basis."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"However, what is different for a partnership is that each partner is liable for all the debts of the partnership and assets can"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"be seized to pay off debts incurred by the partnership irrespective of which partner incurred the debt. In other words"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"a partnership has unlimited liability and partners are regarded as both jointly and severally liable for the debts of the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"partnership."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Management of the partnership is normally shared among the partners. It is common practice to have a Deed of"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Partnership prepared which specifies the agreements between partners. If no such deed is prepared, in the event of a"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"dispute the Partnership Act of 1890 governs the arrangement between the partners."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Profits (income less expenditure) are normally divided equally between the partners, unless the partnership deed specifies"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"otherwise."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Each partner is individually responsible to account to the Inland Revenue and Contributions Agency for their earnings."}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"Probably the greatest single advantage of a partnership is the combination of lack of formal regulation coupled with the"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"fact that you are not alone in making decisions and \u201crunning\u201d the business. Having several people with particular strengths"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"working well together can produce a very potent combination. However, as for the sole trader, if things go wrong,"}}
{"prompt":"An Introduction to Yacht Brokerage","examples":{"text":"everything, in terms of wealth, is at stake."}}
